
Stack(1.0 ver)  ->  Vector(1.0 ver)  ->  List(1.2 ver)  ->  Collection
                LinkedList(1.2 ver)  ->  List
                 ArrayList(1.2 ver)  ->  List

ArrayList:
Resizable and Growable
Duplicated allowed
Insertion order is followed
Heterogeneous objects are allowed (except TreeSet & TreeMap)
Null insertion possible

LinkedList:
Double Linked List is the underlying Data Structure
Insertion order is maintained
Duplicates are allowed
Heterogeneous Objects are allowed
null is allowed

Vector:
Resizable and growable array
duplicate objects is allowed
Insertion order is preserved
null insertion is possible
Heterogeneous objects are allowed
Vector class implemented Serializable, Clonable and RandomAccess interface
Vector is Thread safe as most of the methods are synchronized

Stack:
Child class of vector.
Works on LIFO order.


Set:
Duplication not allowed and Order is not preserved
TreeSet (1.2 ver) -> NavigableSet (1.6 ver) -> SortedSet (1.2 ver) -> Set (1.2 ver) -> Collection (1.2 ver)
                    LinkedHashSet (1.4 ver) ->   HashSet (1.2 ver) -> Set

HashSet:
Hashtable
Duplicated not allowed.
Order is not preserved. Inserted based on hashcode
Heterogeneous are allowed
null insertion is possible
implements Serializable, Clonable interfaces but not RandomAccess
HashSet is the best choice if our frequent is Search Operation

LinkedHashSet:
Best to develop cache based applications, where duplicates are not allowed and insertion order must be followed.
Child class of HashSet

            HashSet                                         LinkedHashSet
1) The underlying data structure is Hash table          The underlying data structure is Hash table + Linked List
2) Insertion order is not preserved                     Insertion order is preserved
3) 1.2 ver                                              1.4 ver

TreeSet:
Data structure: Balanced Tree
Duplicated are not allowed
Insertion order doesn't follow but inserted in sorted form
Heterogeneous not allowed. If tried runtime exception: ClassCastException
Null insertion is allowed but only once